  <refsection id="Description_GEN_SQR">
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
This block is a square wave generator. The output switches between the Minimum value and the maximum value periodicly. The value of the fourth parameter of this block defines the period of the signal. The period of the switching is equal to the period of the signal divided by 2.  
</para>
    <para>
</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection id="Dialogbox_GEN_SQR">
    <title>Dialog box</title>
    <para>
      <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../../../images/GEN_SQR_gui.gif" align="center" valign="middle"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject>
    </para>
    <para>

</para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">Minimum Value</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para> The Lower bound of the generator.</para>
        <para> Properties : Type 'mat' of size [-1,-1]. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">Maximum Value</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para> The upper bound of the generator.</para>
        <para> Properties : Type 'mat' of size [-1,-1]. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">Initial Value( 1= Minimum Value 2= Maximum Value)</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para> When this parameter is set to 1, the initial value of the signal will be the lower bound. When it is set to 2, the initial value will be the upper bound. In else case, it generates an error.</para>
        <para> Properties : Type 'pol' of size -1. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">Period (sec)</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para> The period of the square wave.</para>
        <para> Properties : Type 'pol' of size -1.</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </refsection>
